Acting Health Minister Mmamoloko Kubayi-Ngubane says urgent action is needed to curb the spread of the Delta variant. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the nation on Sunday night. Ramaphosa is expected to discuss government's response to a new, highly transmittable variant responsible for the third wave sweeping across Gauteng. The president will meet with the National Coronavirus Command Council before his address. READ: Delta variant contributing to high COVID-19 infections in SA Acting Health Minister Mmamoloko Kubayi-Ngubane says urgent action is needed to curb the spread of the Delta variant. eNCA will bring the president's address at 8pm on DStv channel 403 and eNCA.com.